<% content_for :subject, "Test Driven Rails" %>

<div class="text-box-wrapper">
  <div class="text-box">
    <hgroup class="product-title">
      <h2>Test Driven Rails Resources</h2>
    </hgroup>

    <h3 id="high-level-design">High-Level Design</h3>
    <ul>
      <li class="subscription">
        <a class="book" href="http://www.amazon.com/Clean-Code-Handbook-Software-Craftsmanship/dp/0132350882/?tag=giantrobotssm-20">
          <span>Clean Code: A Handbook of Agile Software Craftsmanship</span>
          <p>The quintessential book on good software practices.</p>
        </a>
      </li>

      <li class="subscription">
        <a class="book" href="http://www.amazon.com/Design-Patterns-Elements-Reusable-Object-Oriented/dp/0201633612/?tag=giantrobotssm-20">
          <span>Design Patterns: Elements of Reusable Object-Oriented Software</span>
          <p>The quintessential book on design patterns and how to apply them.</p>
        </a>
      </li>

      <li class="star">
        <a class="book" href="http://www.amazon.com/RSpec-Book-Behaviour-Development-Cucumber/dp/1934356379/?tag=giantrobotssm-20">
          <span>The RSpec Book</span>
          <p>Written by David Chelimsky, lead developer of RSpec.</p>
        </a>
      </li>

      <li>
        <a class="book" href="http://www.amazon.com/Working-Effectively-Legacy-Michael-Feathers/dp/0131177052/?tag=giantrobotssm-20">
          <span>Working Effectively with Legacy Code</span>
          <p>The perfect book to read when adding tests to existing applications.</p>
        </a>
      </li>

      <li>
        <a href="http://www.elabs.se/blog/15-you-re-cuking-it-wrong">
          <span>You're Cuking It Wrong</span>
          <p>How <em>not</em> to write acceptance tests.</p>
        </a>
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h3 id="testing-concepts">Testing Concepts</h3>
    <ul>
      <li class="subscription">
        <a class="site" href="http://xunitpatterns.com/Four%20Phase%20Test.html">
          <span>Four-Phase Test</span>
          <p>Setup, Exercise, Verify, Teardown.</p>
        </a>
      </li>

      <li class="subscription">
        <a class="site" href="http://www.jamesshore.com/Blog/Red-Green-Refactor.html">
          <span>Red, Green, Refactor</span>
          <p>Outlines steps to work towards working software in a quick manner.</p>
        </a>
      </li>

      <li class="star">
        <a class="site" href="http://dannorth.net/whats-in-a-story/">
          <span>What's in a Story?</span>
          <p>Discusses outside-in development through BDD.</p>
        </a>
      </li>

      <li class="star">
        <a class="site" href="http://xunitpatterns.com/Mocks,%20Fakes,%20Stubs%20and%20Dummies.html">
          <span>Mocks, Fakes, Stubs, and Dummies</span>
          <p>Breakdown of different types of test doubles and their purposes.</p>
        </a>
      </li>

      <li class="star">
        <a class="video" href="http://cleancoder.posterous.com/100-test-coverage">
          <span>100% Test Coverage</span>
          <p>"Uncle Bob" Martin discussing test coverage.</p>
        </a>
      </li>

      <li class="star">
        <a class="site" href="http://martinfowler.com/bliki/SelfInitializingFake.html">
          <span>Self-Initializing Fake</span>
          <p>A method of testing third-party services by recording real requests and replaying responses.</p>
        </a>
      </li>

      <li>
        <a class="site" href="http://martinfowler.com/articles/mocksArentStubs.html">
          <span>Mocks Aren't Stubs</span>
          <p>Mocks, stubs, and how they differ.</p>
        </a>
      </li>

      <li>
        <a class="site" href="http://tech.groups.yahoo.com/group/extremeprogramming/message/111829">
          <span>Unit Test Rulz [sic]</span>
          <p>Michael Feathers' list on what makes (or doesn't) a unit test.</p>
        </a>
      </li>

      <li>
        <a class="site" href="http://xunitpatterns.com/Obscure%20Test.html">
          <span>xUnit Patterns: Obscure Test</span>
          <p>List of various types of obscure tests (mystery guest, general fixture, eager test).</p>
        </a>
      </li>

      <li>
        <a class="site" href="http://martinfowler.com/articles/nonDeterminism.html#RemoteServices">
          <span>Eradicating Non-Determinism in Tests: Remote Services</span>
          <p>Outlines various ways in which a developer can test against a third-party service.</p>
        </a>
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h3 id="continuous-integration">Continuous Integration</h3>
    <ul>
      <li class="subscription">
        <a class="site" href="http://martinfowler.com/articles/continuousIntegration.html">
          <span>Continuous Integration</span>
          <p>Basic outline of continuous integration.</p>
        </a>
      </li>

      <li class="star">
        <a class="app" href="https://travis-ci.org/">
          <span>Travis CI</span>
          <p>Continuous integration for open-source software.</p>
        </a>
      </li>

      <li>
        <a class="app" href="https://www.tddium.com/">
          <span>tddium by Solano Labs</span>
          <p>Continuous integration in the cloud.</p>
        </a>
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h3 id="testing-tools">Testing Tools</h3>
    <ul>
      <li class="subscription">
        <a class="site" href="https://www.relishapp.com/rspec">
          <span>RSpec</span>
          <p>BDD for Ruby.</p>
        </a>
      </li>

      <li class="subscription">
        <a class="site" href="https://github.com/jnicklas/capybara">
          <span>Capybara</span>
          <p>Acceptance testing framework for web applications.</p>
        </a>
      </li>

      <li class="subscription">
        <a class="site" href="http://pivotal.github.com/jasmine/">
          <span>Jasmine</span>
          <p>BDD for JavaScript.</p>
        </a>
      </li>

      <li>
        <a class="site" href="https://github.com/bmabey/email-spec">
          <span>Email Spec</span>
          <p>Test email delivery more easily.</p>
        </a>
      </li>

      <li>
        <a class="site" href="http://rubydoc.info/gems/simplecov/frames">
          <span>Simplecov</span>
          <p>C0 code coverage for Ruby 1.9.</p>
        </a>
      </li>

      <li>
        <a class="site" href="https://github.com/thoughtbot/capybara-webkit">
          <span>capybara-webkit</span>
          <p>Capybara driver that uses QtWebKit for faster tests.</p>
        </a>
      </li>

      <li>
        <a class="site" href="https://github.com/travisjeffery/timecop">
          <span>Timecop</span>
          <p>A gem providing "time travel" and "time freezing" capabilities.</p>
        </a>
      </li>

      <li>
        <a class="site" href="https://github.com/thoughtbot/factory_bot">
          <span>FactoryBot</span>
          <p>Build objects for your tests.</p>
        </a>
      </li>

      <li>
        <a class="site" href="https://github.com/thoughtbot/bourne">
          <span>Bourne</span>
          <p>Test spies with mocha.</p>
        </a>
      </li>

      <li>
        <a class="app" href="https://codeclimate.com/">
          <span>Code Climate</span>
          <p>Hosted static analysis for Ruby source code.</p>
        </a>
      </li>

      <li>
        <a class="site" href="https://github.com/cucumber/aruba">
          <span>Aruba</span>
          <p>Support for testing CLIs.</p>
        </a>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>

